Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.47,0:22:21.22,Default,ed,0,0,0,,There is one song I cannot ever forget
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.22,0:22:26.85,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Still, there's a face I'm willing to forget
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.85,0:22:29.81,Default,ed,0,0,0,,With her feelings messed up,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.81,0:22:32.69,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Alice got completely lost
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.69,0:22:37.88,Default,ed,0,0,0,,The midst of summer \NBrought her into one tricky love maze
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.20,0:22:44.79,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I want you to hug tightly\NAnd never let go of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.79,0:22:50.17,Default,ed,0,0,0,,One scared and timid tiny girl
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.17,0:22:57.05,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I quite remember our very first kiss \NAnd the beginning of all of this
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.63,0:23:03.47,Default,ed,0,0,0,,While birds were singing for us...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.54,0:23:12.66,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I'll take a car and take a lonely trip
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.66,0:23:17.86,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I know it'll bring me \NTo the seashore
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.86,0:23:20.91,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Where only the the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.91,0:23:23.95,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Dazzlingly bright,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.95,0:23:29.48,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Could witness my long-awaited happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.52,0:01:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,4-1. \NBroir lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.00,0:01:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Marchesa Broir's play was steady, \Nbut Ryuzaki didn't let her have it her way.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.44,0:01:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The fourteen-years-old prodigy and the Queen \Nof Japanese Amateurs will compete for the ball today!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.96,0:02:15.96,Default,,0,0,116,,{\bord4\blur15\3c&HAC907F&\t(0,1100,\bord0\blur0.55)\c&HFEFEFD&\fnGabriola\fs48\frz360\3a&H2D&\fscx144\fscy126}Episode 11 \N\N\N\N \NIt won't fly, anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.28,0:02:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Todo?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.41,0:02:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This one... can't yet return.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.02,0:02:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Until January end, \Nhe has to prepare for his own match.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.05,0:02:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No interruptions to the training pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.42,0:02:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka might not take it easy without him...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.41,0:02:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Wherever he is,\Nhe'll surely be rooting for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.94,0:02:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning Todo has matured that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.99,0:02:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope. I just commanded him to stay. \NHad to push him back into the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.46,0:02:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You got used to the role well, manager-sadist!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.97,0:02:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Demon, if so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.95,0:02:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, sure, demon-manager!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.71,0:03:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, \Nwanna see how she's hands and feet in training?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.54,0:03:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. \NThat's pretty much what I came back for.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.28,0:03:11.49,Default,,0,0,10,,{\an8\b0\fnVerdana}Queen's Cup '90 \NThird Round \NQuarter-finals
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.49,0:03:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Round three. Oka played with Natasha Dollis. \N6-3 and 6-4 tight victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.76,0:03:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,While {\i1}her{\i0} match was much more troublesome...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.56,0:03:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. First match of the third round. \NMarchesa Broir vs. Ryuzaki Reika.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.04,0:03:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In the course of the first set, \NBroir was holding a huge lead with a 5-1 score.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.11,0:03:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly then had to transform.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.65,0:03:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Transform?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.65,0:03:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The usual Madame Butterfly's exalted and noble play \Nwas crushed to pieces!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.67,0:04:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It was unbelievable, Chiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.34,0:04:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,During their fierce battle, \Nthe one once called the Strongest Queen,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.67,0:04:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,distinguished for her perfect footwork, \NMadame Butterfly was not herself!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.11,0:04:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Throwing the pride away, \Nshe switched to baseline tactics.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.42,0:04:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.27,0:04:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,she was no longer looking down on the opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.30,0:04:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She switched the strategy to the receive-only.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.89,0:04:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,However little her chances were,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.79,0:04:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,never has she done that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.36,0:04:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Broir continued to attack,\Nbut the ball was steadily hit back from the baseline.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.96,0:04:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a novice that met a superior opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.77,0:04:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,One could see her saying \N"I am not yet skilled enough to go on the offensive!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.91,0:04:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Desperately \Ntrying to avoid mistakes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.37,0:04:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking only \Nabout receive, receive and receiving!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.79,0:04:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Until the very end of this game, \Nshe never dared to make even a step forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.05,0:04:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone was seeing such a Madame Butterfly's \Nmatch performance for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.63,0:05:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the result has exceeded all expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.15,0:05:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,With receive line strategy, Madame Butterfly \Ntricked Broir who was too green yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.87,0:05:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time, the opponent\Nstonewalled her intense attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.11,0:05:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Broir's pace was completely disrupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.18,0:05:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Time after time, \Nshe was making harsher mistakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.63,0:05:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,ultimately leading to self-destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.68,0:05:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Out! 7-5, 6-3.\NMatch won by... Ryuzaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.14,0:05:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki still managed to win!\NNext she's to fight for a spot in the finals!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.25,0:05:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Victory is victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.25,0:06:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,However, for the sake of achieving it,\NMadame Butterfly had to stop being Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.33,0:06:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But she won after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.86,0:06:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Against the other opponent, \Nit won't work the second time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.37,0:06:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want Madame Butterfly \Nto ever again play a match like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.84,0:06:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.44,0:06:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly said, \Nshe'd prefer to remain an amateur for the rest of her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.81,0:06:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,To keep playing her own tennis \Nand never cheat on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.43,0:06:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Abstained from victories and defeats...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.35,0:06:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So that Madame Butterfly could remain Madame Butterfly, \Nand not someone else!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.38,0:06:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She can still keep winning. \NMadame Butterfly decides her destiny herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.49,0:06:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The matter is, that she can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.02,0:06:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone with renewed strength \Nwill come and defeat her one day!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.93,0:06:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not even a pro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.53,0:06:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonetheless, victory and defeat bother me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.91,0:06:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.70,0:06:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.84,0:06:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Even I know, she herself \Ndoesn't want it to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.81,0:06:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You now have so much to take care of, \NMadame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.44,0:06:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.05,0:07:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.86,0:07:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.93,0:07:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.36,0:07:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet you missed me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.83,0:07:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.67,0:07:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really letting me to stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.57,0:07:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any match tomorrow, \Nand such a beautiful night view is not to be observed alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.86,0:07:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the semi-finals are finally here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.53,0:07:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, the day after tomorrow \NQueen's Cup '90 semifinals'
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.06,0:07:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,matchups are announced.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.73,0:07:34.80,Default,,0,0,10,,{\an8\b0\fnVerdana}Ling Kowon (China) vs. Oka Hiromi (Park Hill Affiliated)\NGene Ryder (America) vs. Reika Ryuzaki (Park Hill Affiliated)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.80,0:07:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, what kind of player is this Ling Kowon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.44,0:07:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly is now facing \Nthe tournament's number one favourite Ryder?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.44,0:07:40.99,Default,,0,0,10,,{\an8\b0\fnVerdana}Gene Ryder              Reika Ryuzaki
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.66,0:07:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly will win,\Nand Hiromi will also win!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.46,0:07:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,At last, the final dream showdown will occur!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.87,0:07:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this? \NWhy the long faces?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.17,0:07:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, take a quick look here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.44,0:07:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.14,0:08:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Cool, isn't it? \NI just learned this one recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.05,0:08:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Maki...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.05,0:08:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly won today, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.95,0:08:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, she did!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.95,0:08:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Though she won, \Nit felt strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.36,0:08:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Strange indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.19,0:08:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Senior Ryuzaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.35,0:08:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations on your victory and advancement... \Nto the semifinals...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.60,0:08:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I will also...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.47,0:08:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Hiromi. \NGood luck in the semifinals, to you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.21,0:08:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,She must have been crying...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.81,0:08:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.82,0:08:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would a winner be weeping?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.42,0:08:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.65,0:08:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But... But... This was the first time \NI saw Madame Butterfly being so lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You're through to the Sealine Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.87,0:09:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to speak to Mr. Katsura Daigo?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.86,0:09:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, Mr. Katsura \Nhas already checked out at 6 pm today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.86,0:09:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Although by tomorrow's night \Nwe expect him to check back in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.61,0:09:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going all of a sudden, Reika?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.76,0:09:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my responsibility \Nto never let the today's match happen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.25,0:09:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, father, to the day after tomorrow's battle \Nwith Gene Ryder, I must arrive perfectly prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.41,0:09:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.70,0:10:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm all ears. How did you end up here? \NWhat might Ochou need in such place?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.40,0:10:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If Hiromi can do it, \Nthere's no way I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.48,0:10:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,She only hits the bouncing ball back
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.41,0:10:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in its lowest position.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.93,0:10:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I know coach Munakata was planning this technique \Nto become her trump card ever since he was training her himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.40,0:10:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to play like this too. \NWant to keep my dignity!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.62,0:10:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't say I'm happy with this.\NIt will destroy your own tennis.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.78,0:10:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, \Nit's already destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.46,0:10:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Back in the tournament's first round, \NHiromi showed me her brilliant acquisition of this technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.90,0:10:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, day by day, day by day, \NHiromi was raising her superiority over me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.61,0:10:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Gradually widening the gap between us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.31,0:10:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether I'm asleep, whether I'm awake, \NI can only think about how helpless I feel holding a racket now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.31,0:10:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as I am obsessed with such thoughts, \Neverything else slips away from my sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.44,0:11:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, coach Katsura, tell me,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.44,0:11:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that you will help me defeat Gene Ryder...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.59,0:11:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And to let me stand \Non the same court with Hiromi in finals...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.44,0:11:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you will do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.23,0:11:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, \Nmy own tennis is already done for!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.56,0:11:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Still I desperately wish \Nto be a worthy Oka Hiromi's opponent!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.14,0:11:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only if I lose to her,\NI can regret nothing afterwards!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.32,0:11:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you take one more step, Ochou!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.06,0:11:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You've always willingly stepped out before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.18,0:11:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can't you take \Njust one extra step away from the line?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.68,0:11:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to stay put. You yourself have created this line. \NJust take a huge step the hell away from it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.70,0:11:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really believe \Nyou can learn anything in a night or two?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.75,0:11:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,For over than twenty years you've been taught \Nto believe only in this, your own, line!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.21,0:11:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Until you cast it off, \Nwe won't get anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.98,0:12:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This way we won't even budge!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.55,0:12:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.99,0:12:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The first night has just begun!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.89,0:12:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time in 20 years, \NI'm being shown what I'm worth!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.99,0:12:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit dreaming!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.59,0:12:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.38,0:12:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Since when did you start \Nliving in the world of fantasies?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.59,0:12:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,30-15.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.75,0:12:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Great performance, Oka!\NIn the semi-final match her opponent is Ling Kowon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.64,0:12:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, Oka hits one return ace after another!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.54,0:13:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout this tournament, \NOka's strength never ceases to amaze!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.14,0:13:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,After seeing Oka's second and third round matches, \NI can finally say for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.25,0:13:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to how she played before, \Nshe showed significant growth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.77,0:13:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What... do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.62,0:13:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say the reception position shifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.59,0:13:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Position of reception?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.81,0:13:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Although I had to look closer to notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.34,0:13:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Her timing for hitting a bouncing ball is a few seconds earlier, \Ncompared to other players.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.03,0:13:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, explaining it to a layman might prove intricate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.13,0:13:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple of seconds, \Nor rather, about 10-20 centimetres lower -
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.24,0:13:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that's where, unlike the other players, she hits the ball.\NThis is how I see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.09,0:13:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's supposed to mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.73,0:13:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In tennis, the deliberate choice of such timing \Nis against common sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.35,0:13:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe, \Nbut the more I look, the more I see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.54,0:13:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How unusual...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.64,0:13:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Previously Oka definitely didn't play like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.06,0:13:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you dare to neglect reporting to America \Nabout such a change?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.63,0:13:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted you to see it with your own eyes, first handedly. \NYou and Todo, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.53,0:14:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it's so unusual \Nthat you wouldn't believe me anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.48,0:14:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka is already \Nundoubtedly making it to the final.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.50,0:14:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, another 10 minutes, and it's decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.26,0:14:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry... Is she asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.52,0:14:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We made it back in town just this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.39,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine, she couldn't sleep a wink \Nsince the day before yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.36,0:14:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,How peculiar.\NHope she'll have a steady hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.65,0:14:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa, since she was a child, \Nshe has always acted like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.65,0:14:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Not always to such an extreme degree, \Nbut in general, it's always this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.24,0:14:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Though I never let this side of her temper \Nto become public.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.51,0:14:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This child has suffered more than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.88,0:14:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And did as much endeavour.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.03,0:14:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if she would've been better off without tennis.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.68,0:14:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows where would she be now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.19,0:14:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, she'd be rosy, \Naffectionate and night-sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.12,0:14:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Joyful people person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.89,0:14:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the way she was before all of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.55,0:15:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong. \NActually...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.40,0:15:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not because of tennis,\Nthe reason is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.34,0:15:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Working till exhaustion is just in her genes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.54,0:15:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But also is to suffer as much.\NThat's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.94,0:15:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why... Shouldn't you be proud \Nof bringing up such an incredible daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.08,0:15:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.22,0:15:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I will watch. Closely. \NOn every single one of her hits.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.89,0:15:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell her no more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.61,0:15:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Great work, Oka!\NYou got yourself a spot in the final!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.59,0:15:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed! \NShe's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.35,0:15:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice play!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.95,0:15:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.25,0:16:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.79,0:16:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.79,0:16:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.26,0:16:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.10,0:16:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Show it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.40,0:16:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a couple of blisters burst. \NBut aside that, nothing serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.80,0:16:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,For safety reasons,\Nwe must immediately disinfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.14,0:16:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.34,0:16:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already come this far.\NKeep up the good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.67,0:16:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, let's proceed. \NThe second match of the semi-final stage starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.16,0:16:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika, it's time to go.\NWake up Reika.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.94,0:16:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Has Hiromi won her match, father?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.16,0:16:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The scores are 6-1 and 6-2. \NShe fought brilliantly and earned a spot in the final.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.88,0:17:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case I should do my best too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.00,0:17:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Best of three set match.\NService play: Ryder!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.92,0:17:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,At once, Ryder seizes the initiative. \NNo wonder she's the tournament's main card.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.18,0:17:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The Tournament's favourite number one, \NGene Ryder vs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.98,0:17:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the Japanese Amateur Tennis Queen, \Nthe famous Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.83,0:17:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever wins this game, \Nthis person will play with Oka in the final round.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.19,0:17:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,30-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.11,0:17:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The serve power difference \Nis obvious right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.76,0:17:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryder holds seventh in the world rankings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.10,0:17:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Her not winning this tournament would be rather odd, \Nespecially given she's still an ascending player.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.09,0:18:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I see... This girl isn't as young and frivolous as Broir. \NShe's really a seasoned pro!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.38,0:18:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Alright...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.67,0:18:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I {\i1}will{\i0} do it after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.34,0:18:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Withdraw, Ochou! \NYou'll never be able to hit like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.83,0:18:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One or two successful hits \Nduring the training mean nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.18,0:18:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In an actual match you'll fail!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.85,0:18:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen well! You'll never be able to repeat what Oka does, \Nbut not because your techniques are weaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.84,0:18:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of techniques, the ones of yours \Nare a level or two higher than hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.69,0:18:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's... That's precisely why \Nyou'll never be able to repeat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.84,0:18:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Your muscle memory will be bounding you to your techniques. \NIt's gonna constantly hit the brakes in your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.37,0:19:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be embraced by mistakes' anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.47,0:19:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Should you need courage for another half-step forward, \Nyou'll brake!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.50,0:19:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll hesitate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.37,0:19:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The better your own tennis is honed, \Nthe severer your mistakes' anxiety will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.61,0:19:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.44,0:19:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,countless outstanding players before you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.61,0:19:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to eliminate mistakes, \Naccustomed their bodies to tennis on reflexes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.43,0:19:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand now, Ochou? \NMunakata after picking Oka who knew nothing then,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.39,0:19:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't bother eliminating mistakes, \Nbut instead made her take half a step onwards!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.22,0:19:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That was his teachings' point the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.44,0:19:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything he had... Including the rest of his life, \Nhe put everything into her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.07,0:19:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why... Oka was able to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.70,0:19:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And why you won't be able to do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.14,0:19:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, coach Katsura.\NDespite everything, I'll still give it a try.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.71,0:19:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm used to overcoming myself.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.48,0:19:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Should I need the courage for one more step forward, \NI will find it by all means!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.12,0:19:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Not only here and now,\Nstanding on this court,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.62,0:19:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but hereafter, \Nfor the sake of my future!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.43,0:20:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.22,0:20:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I was able to hit it before...\NAnd I overcame anxiety countless times...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.29,0:20:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.36,0:20:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I need my courage!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.57,0:20:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I must be able to...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.09,0:20:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Received!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.06,0:20:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly has...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.13,0:20:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly has...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.18,0:20:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Lost!?...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.63,0:21:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,6-1, 6-0. \NSet count: two against zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.86,0:21:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Match won by... Ryder!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.30,0:21:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She has lost! \NMadame Butterfly has lost the match!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.81,0:21:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you still sure \Nit's fine if I come?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.60,0:21:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Reika, you have a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.67,0:21:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.34,0:21:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What, child?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.41,0:21:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry...\NReika will not... fly anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.63,0:23:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Aikawa Maki!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.81,0:23:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Queen's Cup '90 finals!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.78,0:23:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But this all feels somehow unbelievable - \NHiromi's opponent is sadly not Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.89,0:23:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so worried about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.45,0:23:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it's thanks to Madame Butterfly, \NHiromi could make it this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.56,0:23:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be mourning about that, Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.53,0:23:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're still here. Still here, you are! \NAnd you should definitely win!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.70,0:24:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Closing episode: "FINAL STAGE."